<Link id="l00474" /><CodeLine lineNumber="474"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Combine two sets of facts about the same value into a single set of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00475" /><CodeLine lineNumber="475"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// facts.  Note that this method is not suitable for merging facts along</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00476" /><CodeLine lineNumber="476"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// different paths in a CFG; that&#39;s what the mergeIn function is for.  This</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00477" /><CodeLine lineNumber="477"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// is for merging facts gathered about the same value at the same location</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00478" /><CodeLine lineNumber="478"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// through two independent means.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00479" /><CodeLine lineNumber="479"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Notes:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00480" /><CodeLine lineNumber="480"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// &#42; This method does not promise to return the most precise possible lattice</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00481" /><CodeLine lineNumber="481"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   value implied by A and B.  It is allowed to return any lattice element</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00482" /><CodeLine lineNumber="482"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   which is at least as strong as &#42;either&#42; A or B (unless our facts</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00483" /><CodeLine lineNumber="483"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   conflict, see below).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00484" /><CodeLine lineNumber="484"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// &#42; Due to unreachable code, the intersection of two lattice values could be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00485" /><CodeLine lineNumber="485"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   contradictory.  If this happens, we return some valid lattice value so</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00486" /><CodeLine lineNumber="486"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   as not confuse the rest of LVI.  Ideally, we&#39;d always return Undefined,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00487" /><CodeLine lineNumber="487"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   but we do not make this guarantee.  TODO: This would be a useful</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00488" /><CodeLine lineNumber="488"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   enhancement.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
